Enum LogURLParameterType

All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<LogURLParameterType>
public enum LogURLParameterType
extends Enum<LogURLParameterType>

A LogURLParameterType defines the type of data contained in a LogURLParameter.

Parameter types are used by LogMX to render the "Open log file" dialog and to check LogURL parameters validity.

Since:
LogMX v1.2.2
Author:
LightySoft (Xavier Tello)
See Also:

PASSWORD

public static final LogURLParameterType PASSWORD
Denotes a user password, which can be any value of String. Use this parameter type if you don't want to use LogMX password repository. The user will then have to re-type his password each time the Manager wants to access a resource.

To use LogMX password repository, see LogFileManager.getOrAskUserPassword(String, String)
